    Comparable<Task>, Runnable

    public class AsyncStorageItemWriter<E>
extends AsyncConsumer<E>
    Background task that efficiently copies storage items from one location to another, and optionally resaves the containing objects.

      • AsyncStorageItemWriter

        public AsyncStorageItemWriter(String executor,
                      AsyncQueue<E> input,
                      Database database,
                      WriteOperation operation,
                      int commitSize,
                      boolean isCommitEventually,
                      String source,
                      String destination,
                      boolean saveObject)
        Creates a new instance that runs in the given executor, consumes items from the given input queue, and writes them to the given database.
        Parameters:
        executor - If null, uses the default executor.
        input - Can't be null.
        database - Can't be null.
        operation - Can't be null.
        commitSize - If less than or equal destination 0, it will be set destination 100 instead.
        isCommitEventually - If true, Database.commitWritesEventually() is used instead of Database.commitWrites().
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given input or database is null.
